snippet.textDisplay:
As much as mankind
Loves to believe they
Can predict tomorrow
They can not,
They can not
Even pretend to know
They will indeed awaken
Tomorrow, so try to
Focus on the day
For in this day
Is all you can know
And in this day
Is all you can really
Portent,
Enjoy the frivolity
The laughter
And the joy
For tomorrow hath
No path
And what comes
Now that brings you
A smile, a peace
An inner happiness
Might not be there
Tomorrow
And must sustain
You in memory
For those trails
That will await.
